items.title: Election of taoiseach delayed as Dáil suspended amid disorder
items.description: A row broke out in the Dáil, forcing the suspension of proceedings as the Irish parliament returned to nominate a new taoiseach.

items.title: What Trump has done since taking power
items.description: The Republican has started his second term at a fast pace. Here's a handy guide to waht he's done so far.

items.title: Children among dead as Turkey hotel fire investigation continues
items.description: At least 76 people are known to have died, including children and multiple family members.

items.title: Cat makes three flights in 24 hours after being left on plane
items.description: Mittens was flown three times between New Zealand and Australia after being forgotten in a plane's cargo hold.

items.title: What led to hotel fire disaster at Turkish ski resort?
items.description: Some survivors did not hear a fire alarm and there are claims of failures in the hotel's fire safety.
